<subSubSection id="61A062C8FFBECB0CA7C32B66FD87FD47" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="29053143FFBECB0CA7C32B66FD87FD47" blockId="1.[151,1437,562,2036]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198">
<emphasis id="1BCEED51FFBECB0CA7C32B66FED2FD9F" bold="true" box="[151,266,562,587]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Black species with legs whitish yellow, except fore trochanter and femur brownish. Head rounded (
<figureCitation id="B1812DC6FFBECB0CA23A2B66FF7CFDBB" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 7" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1948,1971]" captionTargetBox="[223,1373,200,1911]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[210,1374,193,1921]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 7. Hemerodromia brevicercata sp. nov., 1 – 2, holotype ♂. 3 – 7, paratype ♂. 1, habitus, lateral view; 2, wing; 3, terminalia, lateral view; 4, subepandrial sclerite and epandrium, dorsal view; 5, terminalia, ventral view; 6, phallus, lateral view; 7, apex of the phallus and apex of epandrium, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233673/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="198">
Fig. 
<number id="9F722364FFBECB0CA7C32B03FF7CFDBB" box="[151,164,599,623]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
); cercus much shorter than length of epandrium (
<figureCitation id="B1812DC6FFBECB0CA59A2B02FCCAFDBB" box="[718,786,598,623]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 7" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1948,1971]" captionTargetBox="[223,1373,200,1911]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[210,1374,193,1921]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 7. Hemerodromia brevicercata sp. nov., 1 – 2, holotype ♂. 3 – 7, paratype ♂. 1, habitus, lateral view; 2, wing; 3, terminalia, lateral view; 4, subepandrial sclerite and epandrium, dorsal view; 5, terminalia, ventral view; 6, phallus, lateral view; 7, apex of the phallus and apex of epandrium, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233673/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="198">
Fig. 
<number id="9F722364FFBECB0CA4572B03FCCAFDBB" box="[771,786,599,623]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
); epandrium rather narrower apically, with median row of spine-like setae on inner face (
<figureCitation id="B1812DC6FFBECB0CA6B82B2EFD89FD47" box="[492,593,634,659]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 7" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1948,1971]" captionTargetBox="[223,1373,200,1911]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[210,1374,193,1921]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 7. Hemerodromia brevicercata sp. nov., 1 – 2, holotype ♂. 3 – 7, paratype ♂. 1, habitus, lateral view; 2, wing; 3, terminalia, lateral view; 4, subepandrial sclerite and epandrium, dorsal view; 5, terminalia, ventral view; 6, phallus, lateral view; 7, apex of the phallus and apex of epandrium, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233673/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="198">Figs 5, 7</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="61A062C8FFBECB0CA7932BCAFD03F97B" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" type="description">
<paragraph id="29053143FFBECB0CA7932BCAFC25F958" blockId="1.[151,1437,562,2036]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198">
<emphasis id="1BCEED51FFBECB0CA7932BCAFE89FD63" bold="true" box="[199,337,670,695]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198">Description</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="1BCEED51FFBECB0CA6352BCAFE45FD63" bold="true" box="[353,413,670,695]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198">Male</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="1BCEED51FFBECB0CA6F82BCAFE34FD63" bold="true" box="[428,492,670,695]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198">Head</emphasis>
. Dark brown to black, mouthparts yellow with all setae whitish. Rounded (
<figureCitation id="B1812DC6FFBECB0CA2132BCAFA52FD63" box="[1351,1418,670,695]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 7" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1948,1971]" captionTargetBox="[223,1373,200,1911]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[210,1374,193,1921]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 7. Hemerodromia brevicercata sp. nov., 1 – 2, holotype ♂. 3 – 7, paratype ♂. 1, habitus, lateral view; 2, wing; 3, terminalia, lateral view; 4, subepandrial sclerite and epandrium, dorsal view; 5, terminalia, ventral view; 6, phallus, lateral view; 7, apex of the phallus and apex of epandrium, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233673/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="198">
Fig. 
<number id="9F722364FFBECB0CA2292BCBFA52FD63" box="[1405,1418,671,695]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
); ocellar triangle with 
<number id="9F722364FFBECB0CA6D42B97FE56FD0F" box="[384,398,707,731]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" value="1.0">1</number>
pair of proclinate setae; anterior ocellus larger. Eyes iridescent black, close together on face bearing fine reclinate setulae. Frons with 
<number id="9F722364FFBECB0CA5D62BB3FD74FD2B" box="[642,684,743,767]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" value="1.5" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="1.0">1–2</number>
frontal setulae; 
<number id="9F722364FFBECB0CA43B2BB3FCA5FD2B" box="[879,893,743,767]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" value="1.0">1</number>
pair of distinct vertical setae contiguous with uniseriate row of smaller postocular setae. Occiput bearing scattered fine hairs. Clypeus with rather dense, short downwardly directed pile. Proboscis slightly curved with yellow setae. Antenna with scape and pedicel bearing distinct, short dorsal setulae; postpedicel about 
<number id="9F722364FFBECB0CA5FF2A06FD14FCBF" box="[683,716,850,875]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" value="1.5">1.5</number>
X as long as wide, stylus ~ 
<number id="9F722364FFBECB0CA3562A07FBFDFCBF" box="[1026,1061,851,875]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" value="0.8">0.8</number>
X as long as postpedicel. 
<emphasis id="1BCEED51FFBECB0CA2172A06FA44FCBF" bold="true" box="[1347,1436,850,875]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198">Thorax</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="B1812DC6FFBECB0CA7CB2A22FF3EFC5B" box="[159,230,886,911]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 7" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1948,1971]" captionTargetBox="[223,1373,200,1911]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[210,1374,193,1921]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 7. Hemerodromia brevicercata sp. nov., 1 – 2, holotype ♂. 3 – 7, paratype ♂. 1, habitus, lateral view; 2, wing; 3, terminalia, lateral view; 4, subepandrial sclerite and epandrium, dorsal view; 5, terminalia, ventral view; 6, phallus, lateral view; 7, apex of the phallus and apex of epandrium, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233673/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="198">
Fig. 
<number id="9F722364FFBECB0CA78D2A23FF3EFC5B" box="[217,230,887,911]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
). Short, slightly arched ventrally; dark brown to blackish; antepronotum with anterior margin almost straight and scutum with yellow setae, very small and fine except one notopleural. 
<emphasis id="1BCEED51FFBECB0CA3112ACEFBA5FC67" bold="true" box="[1093,1149,922,947]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198">Legs</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="B1812DC6FFBECB0CA3DA2ACEFB08FC67" box="[1166,1232,922,947]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 7" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1948,1971]" captionTargetBox="[223,1373,200,1911]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[210,1374,193,1921]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 7. Hemerodromia brevicercata sp. nov., 1 – 2, holotype ♂. 3 – 7, paratype ♂. 1, habitus, lateral view; 2, wing; 3, terminalia, lateral view; 4, subepandrial sclerite and epandrium, dorsal view; 5, terminalia, ventral view; 6, phallus, lateral view; 7, apex of the phallus and apex of epandrium, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233673/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="198">
Fig. 
<number id="9F722364FFBECB0CA3972ACFFB08FC67" box="[1219,1232,923,947]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
). Whitish yellow, except fore trochanter and femur brownish. C 
<number id="9F722364FFBECB0CA5C22AEBFD78FC03" box="[662,672,959,983]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" value="1.0">1</number>
~ 
<number id="9F722364FFBECB0CA5E92AEAFD06FC03" box="[701,734,958,983]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" value="1.5">1.5</number>
X longer than distance between C 
<number id="9F722364FFBECB0CA30F2AEBFBBDFC03" box="[1115,1125,959,983]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" value="1.0">1</number>
and C2, 
<date id="5D041783FFBECB0CA39D2AEBFB33FC02" box="[1225,1259,959,982]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198">7X</date>
as long as wide with some pale dorsoapical setae. F 
<number id="9F722364FFBECB0CA5642AB7FDE2FC2F" box="[560,570,995,1019]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" value="1.0">1</number>
about 
<number id="9F722364FFBECB0CA5DD2AB7FD72FC2F" box="[649,682,995,1019]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" value="1.1">1.1</number>
X as long as C 
<number id="9F722364FFBECB0CA40E2AB7FCBDFC2F" box="[858,869,995,1019]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" value="1.0">1</number>
, 3.0– 
<number id="9F722364FFBECB0CA4F12AB6FC1FFC2F" box="[933,967,994,1019]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" value="3.5">3.5</number>
X as long as wide. Femoral formula 
<number id="9F722364FFBECB0CA23F2AB6FA4CFC2F" box="[1387,1428,994,1019]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" value="6.5" valueMax="7.0" valueMin="6.0">
6– 
<date id="5D041783FFBECB0CA2D32AB6FA4CFC2F" box="[1415,1428,994,1019]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" value="1915-07-14" valueMax="1915-07-15" valueMin="1915-07-14">7</date>
</number>
/ 
<number id="9F722364FFBECB0CA7C32D52FF04FBCB" box="[151,220,1030,1055]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" value="14.5" valueMax="15.0" valueMin="14.0">14–15</number>
/ 
<number id="9F722364FFBECB0CA7B22D52FEF4FBCB" box="[230,300,1030,1055]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" value="15.5" valueMax="16.0" valueMin="15.0">15–16</number>
/ 
<number id="9F722364FFBECB0CA6622D52FE87FBCB" box="[310,351,1030,1055]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" value="7.5" valueMax="8.0" valueMin="7.0">7–8</number>
; denticles confined to distal 
<number id="9F722364FFBECB0CA5F72D52FD11FBCB" box="[675,713,1030,1055]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" value="0.6">0.6</number>
, becoming closer together distally, black, 
<number id="9F722364FFBECB0CA3F12D53FB6BFBCB" box="[1189,1203,1031,1055]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" value="2.0">2</number>
rows linear, without distal discontinuity, converging at apex. T 
<number id="9F722364FFBECB0CA5232D7FFD59FB97" box="[631,641,1067,1091]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" value="1.0">1</number>
~ 
<number id="9F722364FFBECB0CA5F52D7EFD1CFB97" box="[673,708,1066,1091]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" value="0.6">0.6</number>
X as long as F 
<number id="9F722364FFBECB0CA43B2D7FFCA2FB97" box="[879,890,1067,1091]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" value="1.0">1</number>
, evenly curved, ventral face shallowly concave; about 
<number id="9F722364FFBECB0CA7B62D1BFEC2FBB3" box="[226,282,1103,1127]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" value="9.5" valueMax="10.0" valueMin="9.0">9–10</number>
sharply pointed spinose setae ventrally; dorsal ciliation of decumbent short, pale setulae, denser distally; without apicoventral extension on T 
<number id="9F722364FFBECB0CA5CC2D27FD7AFB5F" box="[664,674,1139,1163]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" value="1.0">1</number>
but with strong, black subapical spine. Mid- and hind legs slender with fine setae; T 
<number id="9F722364FFBECB0CA6312DC3FEA9FB7B" box="[357,369,1175,1199]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" value="3.0">3</number>
with ‘comb’ of short setae posteroapically. 
<emphasis id="1BCEED51FFBECB0CA4252DC2FC6AFB7B" bold="true" box="[881,946,1174,1199]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198">Wing</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="B1812DC6FFBECB0CA4902DC2FBD4FB7B" box="[964,1036,1174,1199]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 7" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1948,1971]" captionTargetBox="[223,1373,200,1911]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[210,1374,193,1921]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 7. Hemerodromia brevicercata sp. nov., 1 – 2, holotype ♂. 3 – 7, paratype ♂. 1, habitus, lateral view; 2, wing; 3, terminalia, lateral view; 4, subepandrial sclerite and epandrium, dorsal view; 5, terminalia, ventral view; 6, phallus, lateral view; 7, apex of the phallus and apex of epandrium, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233673/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="198">
Fig. 
<number id="9F722364FFBECB0CA4A82DC3FBD4FB7B" box="[1020,1036,1175,1199]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
