~ 
<number id="9F722364FFBECB0CA6E62C5CFE0DFAF5" box="[434,469,1288,1313]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" value="2.5">2.5</number>
X as long as R 
<number id="9F722364FFBECB0CA52C2C43FD58FAF1" box="[632,640,1303,1317]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" value="4.0">4</number>
; cell bm+dm short, ending at level of R 
<number id="9F722364FFBECB0CA36B2C43FB9FFAF1" box="[1087,1095,1303,1317]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" value="1.0">1</number>
, ~ 
<date id="5D041783FFBECB0CA3372C5CFB5EFAF4" box="[1123,1158,1288,1312]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198">
<number id="9F722364FFBECB0CA3372C5CFBA9FAF4" box="[1123,1137,1288,1312]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" value="2.0">2</number>
X
</date>
as long as cell br. Halter whitish yellow. 
<emphasis id="1BCEED51FFBECB0CA6052C7BFE1DFA9C" bold="true" box="[337,453,1327,1352]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198">Abdomen</emphasis>
. Tergites and sternites brownish; tergite 
<number id="9F722364FFBECB0CA4F02C7BFC6AFA93" box="[932,946,1327,1351]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" value="8.0">8</number>
shorter than sternite 
<number id="9F722364FFBECB0CA3FA2C7BFB66FA93" box="[1198,1214,1327,1351]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" value="8.0">8</number>
. 
<emphasis id="1BCEED51FFBECB0CA39B2C7BFA8AFA9C" bold="true" box="[1231,1362,1327,1352]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198">Terminalia</emphasis>
. Dark brown to black. Cercus very short (
<figureCitation id="B1812DC6FFBECB0CA54A2C07FDB9FABF" box="[542,609,1363,1388]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 7" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1948,1971]" captionTargetBox="[223,1373,200,1911]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[210,1374,193,1921]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 7. Hemerodromia brevicercata sp. nov., 1 – 2, holotype ♂. 3 – 7, paratype ♂. 1, habitus, lateral view; 2, wing; 3, terminalia, lateral view; 4, subepandrial sclerite and epandrium, dorsal view; 5, terminalia, ventral view; 6, phallus, lateral view; 7, apex of the phallus and apex of epandrium, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233673/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="198">
Fig. 
<number id="9F722364FFBECB0CA5062C07FDB9FABF" box="[594,609,1363,1387]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
), not reaching half length of epandrium, wide basally and pointed at apex, left and right cerci closely approximated dorsally, distinctly setose. Epandrium wide, rounded at apex (
<figureCitation id="B1812DC6FFBECB0CA2122C23FA55FA5B" box="[1350,1421,1399,1424]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 7" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1948,1971]" captionTargetBox="[223,1373,200,1911]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[210,1374,193,1921]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 7. Hemerodromia brevicercata sp. nov., 1 – 2, holotype ♂. 3 – 7, paratype ♂. 1, habitus, lateral view; 2, wing; 3, terminalia, lateral view; 4, subepandrial sclerite and epandrium, dorsal view; 5, terminalia, ventral view; 6, phallus, lateral view; 7, apex of the phallus and apex of epandrium, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233673/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="198">
Fig. 
<number id="9F722364FFBECB0CA22A2C23FA55FA5B" box="[1406,1421,1399,1423]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
), distinct strong setae on outer face; median row of stronger setae on inner face (
<figureCitation id="B1812DC6FFBECB0CA3572CCFFBBEFA67" box="[1027,1126,1435,1460]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 7" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1948,1971]" captionTargetBox="[223,1373,200,1911]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[210,1374,193,1921]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 7. Hemerodromia brevicercata sp. nov., 1 – 2, holotype ♂. 3 – 7, paratype ♂. 1, habitus, lateral view; 2, wing; 3, terminalia, lateral view; 4, subepandrial sclerite and epandrium, dorsal view; 5, terminalia, ventral view; 6, phallus, lateral view; 7, apex of the phallus and apex of epandrium, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233673/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="198">Figs 5, 7</figureCitation>
); articulated to hypandrium by weak point anteriorly. Surstylus absent. Hypandrium inflated, rather rounded, with strong setae; gonocoxal apodeme projecting as narrow process just beyond anterior margin of hypandrium. Subepandrial sclerite with short triangular anterior projection; 
<number id="9F722364FFBECB0CA6A22F53FDDCF9CB" box="[502,516,1543,1567]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" value="2.0">2</number>
posterior fine and long finger-like processes with long setae at apex (
<figureCitation id="B1812DC6FFBECB0CA2112F53FA57F9CB" box="[1349,1423,1543,1568]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 7" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1948,1971]" captionTargetBox="[223,1373,200,1911]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[210,1374,193,1921]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 7. Hemerodromia brevicercata sp. nov., 1 – 2, holotype ♂. 3 – 7, paratype ♂. 1, habitus, lateral view; 2, wing; 3, terminalia, lateral view; 4, subepandrial sclerite and epandrium, dorsal view; 5, terminalia, ventral view; 6, phallus, lateral view; 7, apex of the phallus and apex of epandrium, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233673/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="198">
Fig. 
<number id="9F722364FFBECB0CA22A2F53FA57F9CB" box="[1406,1423,1543,1567]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
). Phallus strongly sclerotized (
<figureCitation id="B1812DC6FFBECB0CA68F2F7FFDC7F990" box="[475,543,1579,1604]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 7" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1948,1971]" captionTargetBox="[223,1373,200,1911]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[210,1374,193,1921]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 7. Hemerodromia brevicercata sp. nov., 1 – 2, holotype ♂. 3 – 7, paratype ♂. 1, habitus, lateral view; 2, wing; 3, terminalia, lateral view; 4, subepandrial sclerite and epandrium, dorsal view; 5, terminalia, ventral view; 6, phallus, lateral view; 7, apex of the phallus and apex of epandrium, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233673/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="198">
Fig. 
<number id="9F722364FFBECB0CA55B2F7FFDC7F990" box="[527,543,1579,1604]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
), extending well beyond hypandrium apex, bluntly pointed apically, with apical membranous area, covered with spicules and 
<number id="9F722364FFBECB0CA5C92F1BFD73F9B3" box="[669,683,1615,1639]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" value="2.0">2</number>
dorsal hook-like processes apically (
<figureCitation id="B1812DC6FFBECB0CA3052F1BFB4FF9B3" box="[1105,1175,1615,1640]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 7" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1948,1971]" captionTargetBox="[223,1373,200,1911]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[210,1374,193,1921]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 7. Hemerodromia brevicercata sp. nov., 1 – 2, holotype ♂. 3 – 7, paratype ♂. 1, habitus, lateral view; 2, wing; 3, terminalia, lateral view; 4, subepandrial sclerite and epandrium, dorsal view; 5, terminalia, ventral view; 6, phallus, lateral view; 7, apex of the phallus and apex of epandrium, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233673/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="198">
Fig. 
<number id="9F722364FFBECB0CA3D32F1BFB4FF9B3" box="[1159,1175,1615,1639]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
). Ejaculatory apodeme absent. 
