<subSubSection id="61A062C8FFBECB0CA7932E3BFA54F87F" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="29053143FFBECB0CA7932E3BFC25F853" blockId="1.[151,1437,562,2036]" box="[199,1021,1903,1928]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198">
<emphasis id="1BCEED51FFBECB0CA7932E3BFE9EF85C" bold="true" box="[199,326,1903,1928]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198">Etymology</emphasis>
. From the Latin 
<emphasis id="1BCEED51FFBECB0CA5572E3BFD95F853" box="[515,589,1903,1927]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="198">brevis,</emphasis>
referring to short length of the cercus.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="29053143FFBECB0CA7932EC7FA54F87F" blockId="1.[151,1437,562,2036]" box="[199,1420,1939,1964]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198">
<emphasis id="1BCEED51FFBECB0CA7932EC7FE98F878" bold="true" box="[199,320,1939,1964]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198">Variations</emphasis>
. 
<typeStatus id="F6018FE1FFBECB0CA6042EC0FE65F878" box="[336,445,1940,1964]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198">Paratypes</typeStatus>
with body length varying from 
<quantity id="EE429CA6FFBECB0CA4772EC7FC72F87F" box="[803,938,1939,1963]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.6" metricValueMax="3.1" metricValueMin="2.1" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" unit="mm" value="2.6" valueMax="3.1" valueMin="2.1">2.1–3.1 mm</quantity>
and wing length varying from 
<quantity id="EE429CA6FFBECB0CA2522EC7FA54F87F" box="[1286,1420,1939,1964]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.1" metricValueMax="2.6" metricValueMin="1.6" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" unit="mm" value="2.1" valueMax="2.6" valueMin="1.6">1.6–2.6 mm</quantity>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="61A062C8FFBECB0EA7932EE3FCF7FEB0" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="200" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="29053143FFBECB0EA7932EE3FCF7FEB0" blockId="1.[151,1437,562,2036]" lastBlockId="3.[151,1436,151,357]" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="200" pageId="1" pageNumber="198">
<emphasis id="1BCEED51FFBECB0CA7932EE3FEECF804" bold="true" box="[199,308,1975,2000]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="EEBA4AC0FFBECB0CA6102EE3FD5AF81B" box="[324,642,1975,1999]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Hemerodromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevicercata" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="1BCEED51FFBECB0CA6102EE3FD5AF81B" box="[324,642,1975,1999]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="198">Hemerodromia brevicercata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="00FD502AFFBECB0CA5DF2EE3FD3FF804" box="[651,743,1975,2000]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" rank="species">
<emphasis id="1BCEED51FFBECB0CA5DF2EE3FD3FF804" bold="true" box="[651,743,1975,2000]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
appears to belong to the informal 
<emphasis id="1BCEED51FFBECB0CA32D2EE3FB2FF81B" box="[1145,1271,1975,1999]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="198">empiformis</emphasis>
species group proposed by 
<bibRefCitation id="4D2B4CB2FFBECB0CA6732E8FFE27F827" author="MacDonald" box="[295,511,2011,2036]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" refString="MacDonald, J. F. (1998) Review of the genus Hemerodromia Meigen (Diptera: Empididae: Hemerodromiinae) of America north of Mexico. Proceedings of the Entomological Society of Washington, 100, 792 - 823." type="journal article" year="1998">
MacDonald (
<number id="9F722364FFBECB0CA6EF2E8FFE2FF827" box="[443,503,2011,2035]" pageId="1" pageNumber="198" value="1998.0">1998</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, on the basis of the short cercus, but differs from other species of this group by having a rounded head and different shaped epandrium. 
<taxonomicName id="EEBA4AC0FFBCCB0EA46629CCFBABFF64" box="[818,1139,152,176]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Hemerodromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="200" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevicercata" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="1BCEED51FFBCCB0EA46629CCFBABFF64" box="[818,1139,152,176]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="200">Hemerodromia brevicercata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="00FD502AFFBCCB0EA32A29C3FB04FF64" box="[1150,1244,151,176]" pageId="3" pageNumber="200" rank="species">
<emphasis id="1BCEED51FFBCCB0EA32A29C3FB04FF64" bold="true" box="[1150,1244,151,176]" pageId="3" pageNumber="200">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="EEBA4AC0FFBCCB0EA2D529CDFE48FF01" authority="Melander" authorityName="Melander" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Hemerodromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="200" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="coleophora">
<emphasis id="1BCEED51FFBCCB0EA2D529CDFECFFF00" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="200">H. coleophora</emphasis>
Melander
</taxonomicName>
in sharing a similar shaped cercus (
<figureCitation id="B1812DC6FFBCCB0EA40029E8FC74FF00" box="[852,940,188,213]" captionStart="FIGURES 8 – 14" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1942,1965]" captionTargetBox="[221,1379,196,1912]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[195,1391,193,1921]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 8 – 14. Hemerodromia carioca sp. nov., holotype ♂. 8., habitus, lateral view; 9, wing; 10, terminalia, lateral view; 11, terminalia, dorsal view; 12, subepandrial sclerite, epandrium and surstylus, dorsal view; 13, phallus, ejaculatory apodeme, gonocoxal apodeme, hypandrium, lateral view; 14, terminalia, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233674/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="200">
Fig. 
<number id="9F722364FFBCCB0EA4C429E8FC74FF00" box="[912,940,188,212]" pageId="3" pageNumber="200" value="10.0">10</number>
</figureCitation>
vs. fig. 
<quantity id="EE429CA6FFBCCB0EA34929E8FB85FF01" box="[1053,1117,188,213]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.318" pageId="3" pageNumber="200" unit="in" value="17.0">17 in</quantity>
<bibRefCitation id="4D2B4CB2FFBCCB0EA33F29E8FA99FF00" author="MacDonald" box="[1131,1345,188,213]" pageId="3" pageNumber="200" refString="MacDonald, J. F. (1998) Review of the genus Hemerodromia Meigen (Diptera: Empididae: Hemerodromiinae) of America north of Mexico. Proceedings of the Entomological Society of Washington, 100, 792 - 823." type="journal article" year="1998">
MacDonald, 
<number id="9F722364FFBCCB0EA25129E8FA99FF00" box="[1285,1345,188,212]" pageId="3" pageNumber="200" value="1998.0">1998</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). In 
<taxonomicName id="EEBA4AC0FFBCCB0EA2D529E9FEFBFF2C" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Hemerodromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="200" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevicercata" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="1BCEED51FFBCCB0EA2D529E9FEFBFF2C" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="200">H. brevicercata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="00FD502AFFBCCB0EA67E298BFE5CFF2C" box="[298,388,223,248]" pageId="3" pageNumber="200" rank="species">
<emphasis id="1BCEED51FFBCCB0EA67E298BFE5CFF2C" bold="true" box="[298,388,223,248]" pageId="3" pageNumber="200">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
the head is rounded (
<figureCitation id="B1812DC6FFBCCB0EA52D298BFD63FF2C" box="[633,699,223,248]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 7" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1948,1971]" captionTargetBox="[223,1373,200,1911]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[210,1374,193,1921]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 7. Hemerodromia brevicercata sp. nov., 1 – 2, holotype ♂. 3 – 7, paratype ♂. 1, habitus, lateral view; 2, wing; 3, terminalia, lateral view; 4, subepandrial sclerite and epandrium, dorsal view; 5, terminalia, ventral view; 6, phallus, lateral view; 7, apex of the phallus and apex of epandrium, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233673/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="200">
Fig. 
<number id="9F722364FFBCCB0EA5FA29B4FD63FF2C" box="[686,699,224,248]" pageId="3" pageNumber="200" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
), fore trochanter and femur are brownish (
<figureCitation id="B1812DC6FFBCCB0EA3F4298BFB39FF2C" box="[1184,1249,223,248]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 7" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1948,1971]" captionTargetBox="[223,1373,200,1911]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[210,1374,193,1921]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 7. Hemerodromia brevicercata sp. nov., 1 – 2, holotype ♂. 3 – 7, paratype ♂. 1, habitus, lateral view; 2, wing; 3, terminalia, lateral view; 4, subepandrial sclerite and epandrium, dorsal view; 5, terminalia, ventral view; 6, phallus, lateral view; 7, apex of the phallus and apex of epandrium, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233673/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="200">
Fig. 
<number id="9F722364FFBCCB0EA38129B4FB39FF2C" box="[1237,1249,224,248]" pageId="3" pageNumber="200" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
) and epandrium rather narrower apically, with median row of stronger setae on inner face (
<figureCitation id="B1812DC6FFBCCB0EA48A2850FB9CFEC8" box="[990,1092,260,285]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 7" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1948,1971]" captionTargetBox="[223,1373,200,1911]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[210,1374,193,1921]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 7. Hemerodromia brevicercata sp. nov., 1 – 2, holotype ♂. 3 – 7, paratype ♂. 1, habitus, lateral view; 2, wing; 3, terminalia, lateral view; 4, subepandrial sclerite and epandrium, dorsal view; 5, terminalia, ventral view; 6, phallus, lateral view; 7, apex of the phallus and apex of epandrium, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233673/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="200">Figs 5, 7</figureCitation>
). In 
<taxonomicName id="EEBA4AC0FFBCCB0EA32D2851FAC4FEC8" box="[1145,1308,260,284]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Hemerodromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="200" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="coleophora">
<emphasis id="1BCEED51FFBCCB0EA32D2851FAC4FEC8" box="[1145,1308,260,284]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="200">H. coleophora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the head is flattened dorsoventrally, legs yellowish and epandrium slender and straight basally, and then abruptly enlarged at or slightly beyond the distal third (
<bibRefCitation id="4D2B4CB2FFBCCB0EA6A82818FCFAFEB0" author="MacDonald" box="[508,802,332,357]" pageId="3" pageNumber="200" refString="MacDonald, J. F. (1998) Review of the genus Hemerodromia Meigen (Diptera: Empididae: Hemerodromiinae) of America north of Mexico. Proceedings of the Entomological Society of Washington, 100, 792 - 823." type="journal article" year="1998">
MacDonald, 
<number id="9F722364FFBCCB0EA5C42818FD13FEB0" box="[656,715,332,356]" pageId="3" pageNumber="200" value="1998.0">1998</number>
, fig. 
<number id="9F722364FFBCCB0EA4572818FCFAFEB0" box="[771,802,332,356]" pageId="3" pageNumber="200" value="17.0">17</number>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
